the sun burns high in the sky, filling the area with bright light which shines
on rocks, creating areas of intense brightness, and a few areas of ghastly
shadow.  At night, the air becomes frigid, and all is bathed in the glow of the
moons, becoming an eerie pink when Lunitari rides in the night sky.  It is at
its most beautiful, however, at times of transition.  When the sun is either
rising or sinking.  Then the array of colors in the huge sky reflect upon the
clay soil and rocks, creating a picture to rival even the masterpiece of a
great painter.  The area is barren of plant life, but the rock and soil have an
eerie beauty all their own.  The path continues off to the east and west,
though this particular portion of the road may have perhaps the grandest view
